---
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/?$/, '/');
---
<section id="case-studies" aria-label="Product Marketing experience" class="section">

  <div class="sec-body-grid">
    <div class="sec-left">

      <div class="sec-meta">
        <span class="sec-date">2023 — present</span>
        <span class="sec-company">iConnections</span>
        <span class="sec-industry">FinTech · Alternative Investments</span>
        <span class="sec-date">2023</span>
        <span class="sec-company">VTEX</span>
        <span class="sec-industry">E-commerce · SaaS</span>
      </div>

      <p class="sec-q">"Why should people use this?"</p>
      <h2 class="sec-title">Product Marketing</h2>
      <p class="sec-sub">GTM strategy, product launches, and lifecycle marketing — across two different growth stages.</p>

      <div class="sec-stats">
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">5M+</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">reach · VTEX Vision Spring '24</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">40+</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">products shipped to market</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">17</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">products in single launch</span>
        </div>
        <div class="sec-stat-block">
          <span class="sec-stat-n">300+</span>
          <span class="sec-stat-l">media pieces in 30 days</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="sec-text">I've had the luck of doing PMM in two completely different contexts. At VTEX — a Brazilian-born e-commerce platform I joined at 300 employees and left at 1,300 — I worked campaign-driven GTM, with KPIs tied to lead acquisition, new contracts, and brand awareness. At iConnections, a US company making the shift to product-first, I moved to platform adoption, user research, and engagement. One outbound, one inbound. That range is the point: I learned how to read a business's growth stage and adapt the strategy, rather than repeat a playbook.</p>
      <div class="sec-links">
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cNJBDHKKpMg" class="sec-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">VTEX Vision trailer ↗</a>
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/from-vision-reality-lessons-learned-launching-17-products-meyer-h3hrf/" class="sec-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Behind the scenes: VTEX Vision ↗</a>
        <a href="https://iconnections.io/allocator-pro/" class="sec-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Allocator Pro ↗</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-panels">
      <div class="sec-panel">
        <div class="sec-panel-label">Skills</div>
        <div class="sec-pills">
          <span class="sec-pill">Go-to-Market Strategy</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Product Positioning</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Messaging &amp; Narrative</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Competitive Intelligence</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Seasonal Product Releases</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Lifecycle Marketing</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Platform Adoption</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">User Reengagement</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Member Loyalty Programs</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Sales Enablement</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Win-Loss Analysis</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Campaign Management</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Email Marketing</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Video Production</span>
          <span class="sec-pill">Battle Cards</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="sec-panel">
        <div class="sec-panel-label">Tools</div>
        <div class="sec-pills">
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">HubSpot</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Sendgrid</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Intercom</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Pendo</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Looker</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Salesforce</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">PowerBI</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Screenstudio</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">ElevenLabs</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Descript</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Figma</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Notion</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">Claude</span>
          <span class="sec-pill sec-pill-tool">ChatGPT</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Case card row — full width below the 2-col grid -->
  <div class="sec-cases-row">
    <div class="sec-case-card">
      <div class="sec-case-img">
        <img src={`${base}images/cases/allocator-pro.png`} alt="Allocator Pro" />
      </div>
      <div class="sec-case-type">Lifecycle marketing · B2B loyalty</div>
      <h3 class="sec-case-title">Member Loyalty Program</h3>
      <p class="sec-case-desc">Tier architecture, campaign strategy, in-platform experience, and premium event logistics — built from zero to live product.</p>
      <a href="https://iconnections.io/allocator-pro/" class="sec-case-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View Allocator Pro ↗</a>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-case-card">
      <div class="sec-case-img">
        <img src={`${base}images/cases/vtex-vision-teaser.gif`} alt="VTEX Vision" />
      </div>
      <div class="sec-case-type">Seasonal product release · GTM</div>
      <h3 class="sec-case-title">17-Product Global Launch</h3>
      <p class="sec-case-desc">Sole PMM coordinating 15+ teams and 4 external suppliers. 5M+ reach and 300+ media pieces in 30 days.</p>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/from-vision-reality-lessons-learned-launching-17-products-meyer-h3hrf/" class="sec-case-link" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Behind the scenes ↗</a>
    </div>
    <div class="sec-case-card">
      <div class="sec-case-type">Lifecycle marketing · Reengagement</div>
      <h3 class="sec-case-title">Inactive User Reengagement</h3>
      <p class="sec-case-desc">Structured exploration to identify messaging and value proposition for deeply inactive users — before committing to a full campaign build.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="sec-expand">
    <button class="sec-expand-btn" aria-expanded="false">
      <span class="sec-expand-icon">+</span>
      <span class="sec-expand-label">Why Product Marketing? — the story behind the pivot</span>
    </button>
    <div class="sec-expand-content" hidden>
      <p class="sec-expand-text">I didn't switch to PMM because I was tired of tech writing. I switched because I missed adjectives. I missed caring not just about how a product worked, but about why someone should choose it. I'd spent four years being ruthlessly precise — cutting anything argumentative from docs, marking persuasive language red in VScode diffs — and I was good at it. But the creative, business-facing part of my brain was getting restless. When I mapped the decision as a Venn diagram: what skills do I already have, what do I want to learn next, what roles sit close to revenue — product marketing landed in the center every time. My technical fluency would make me a better PMM. And PMM would give me back the "why."</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>
